Here's the PlantUML sequence diagram for the deployment behavior of the predictive maintenance system:

```plantuml
@startuml odh-labs_predictive-maint
title Predictive Maintenance System Deployment Sequence

actor User
participant "oc CLI" as oc
participant "OpenShift Cluster" as openshift
participant "Docker" as docker
participant "Seldon Core" as seldon
participant "Kafka (Strimzi)" as kafka
participant "MinIO" as minio
participant "Consumer App" as consumer

User -> oc: Run ocp_deploy.py
oc -> docker: Build image from Dockerfile
docker --> oc: Image built
oc -> openshift: Create resources (kubectl apply)
openshift -> kafka: Deploy Kafka cluster (kafka.yaml)
openshift -> minio: Deploy MinIO (minio-full.yaml)
openshift -> seldon: Deploy model (Seldon-Deployment.yaml)
openshift -> consumer: Deploy consumer (consumer-deployment.yaml)

seldon --> openshift: Model deployed
kafka --> openshift: Kafka ready
minio --> openshift: MinIO ready
consumer --> openshift: Consumer running

openshift --> oc: Deployment complete
oc --> User: Deployment successful

User -> openshift: Access web interface
openshift -> minio: Fetch prediction data
minio --> openshift: Return data
openshift --> User: Display dashboard
@enduml
```